Uganda&rsquo;s national ruling party, the national resistance movement NRM has rebutted claims by the ODM party that it was working in cahoots with deputy president William Ruto to destabilize the country. NRM's secretary-general Richard Todwong says Uganda does not and will never interfere with the internal affairs of any country. And as Duncan Khaemba reports, dust on the deputy president&rsquo;s abortive trip could be far from settling down.